YOUR BRAND — MASTER 3D GENERATION PROMPT

This is a controlled 3D asset generation task for your brand.
Customize the visual universe, color palette, materials, and lighting
below to match your brand identity.

====================================================================

VISUAL UNIVERSE

Describe the visual world your 3D assets live in:
- Environment type (e.g., deep-space, underwater, studio, nature)
- Overall mood (e.g., optimistic futurism, dark elegance, playful)
- Key visual elements (e.g., glass morphism, neon, organic shapes)

Core visual DNA:
- Material style 1 (e.g., frosted glass, metallic, matte)
- Material style 2
- Lighting mood (e.g., neon rim light, soft studio, dramatic)
- Texture preferences (e.g., noise overlay, clean, textured)

====================================================================

COLOR PALETTE

PRIMARY ACCENTS:
- Color 1 #hex — description and usage
- Color 2 #hex — description and usage
- Color 3 #hex — description and usage

BACKGROUND:
- Primary background #hex
- Secondary depth layer #hex
- NEVER use: list prohibited background colors

COLOR RULES:
- Which color dominates?
- How do colors interact with materials?
- Shadow color preferences

====================================================================

MATERIAL LIBRARY

List your brand's approved materials:

MATERIAL 1 (e.g., FROSTED GLASS)
- Translucency, clarity, edge behavior
- Light interaction
- Usage: when to use this material

MATERIAL 2 (e.g., METALLIC)
- Surface finish, reflectivity
- Color interaction
- Usage: when to use this material

====================================================================

LIGHTING SYSTEM

Primary light:
- Color and position
- Intensity and purpose

Secondary light:
- Color and position
- Intensity and purpose

Ambient:
- Color and intensity

LIGHTING RULES:
- Mandatory lighting features
- Prohibited lighting styles

====================================================================

FRAMING & CAMERA

- Camera angle preferences
- Subject framing (% of frame)
- Focal length equivalent

